## Description {#details}

Describe a collection of units.

Intended to hold all units either from .debug&#95;info and .debug&#95;types, or from .debug&#95;info.dwo and .debug&#95;types.dwo.

Definition at line 128 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/dwarf/dwarfunit-h">DWARFUnit.h</a>.

### addUnitsForDWOSection() {#ad6aa7a3869850e6b84b875c934cc1144}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void DWARFUnitVector::addUnitsForDWOSection (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfcontext">DWARFContext</a> &amp; C, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfsection">DWARFSection</a> &amp; DWOSection, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a52d529efd96454b48642563c5f78e242">DWARFSectionKind</a> SectionKind, bool Lazy=false)</>}>
Read units from a .debug&#95;info.dwo or .debug&#95;types.dwo section.

Calls made before <a href="#a4c665da429b0ef0e774843d0829ffadb">finishedInfoUnits()</a> are assumed to be for .debug&#95;info.dwo sections, calls after <a href="#a4c665da429b0ef0e774843d0829ffadb">finishedInfoUnits()</a> are for .debug&#95;types.dwo sections. Caller must not mix calls to addUnitsForSection and addUnitsForDWOSection.
